  "description": "Babble, 2025-08-04 09:53 – working with the Org-roam database In this babble I\u0026rsquo;m going to be looking at how to work with the Org-roam database, toward the goal of being able to produce something like Obsidian Dataview queries within my Org-roam files, when they\u0026rsquo;re published to emsenn.net.\nIn looking online, there\u0026rsquo;s folk who use org-roam-db-query to load up the database and search through it with Elisp. But this is wildly inefficient, when there\u0026rsquo;s a where argument that can be set to use the database\u0026rsquo;s search algorithms.\n",
